Mali Death Toll From Cholera Outbreak Rises to 29, Health Ministry Says

-- B y   D i a k a r i d i a   D e m b e l e
-- 
2011-08-08T17:49:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/mali-death-toll-from-cholera-outbreak-rises-to-29-health-ministry-says.html
The death toll in  Mali ’s cholera
outbreak climbed to 29 people, with 552 total cases reported,
said Diallo Madeleine Ba, the country’s minister of health.  The toll accounts for the period from the start of the
outbreak in early July to Aug. 6, she said in a statement read
on state-owned Radio Mali today. The illnesses were reported
in the northeast cities of Timbuktu and Mopti, she said.  Drugs and disinfectants have been made available to the
regions to combat the disease, she said. Cholera, a bacterial
infection, is spread through contaminated water and food.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Diakaridia Dembele via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 